🎉Pika World Markets Update - 5 December 2023🎉The equity markets were broadly lower  as the possibility of a Fed cut next year primarily drove the rally fizzle. Investors took a breather and took chips off the table in what is seen as a surprisingly strong November gain.Without significant economic news except for Factory orders  which saw a larger-than-expected decline  corporate news dominated the headlines for the day.Let us dive into some key highlights.💸Virgin Galacticdived by about 18% as its founder  Richard Branson  indicated that he would not pump further cash into the space tourism business. This might hint at more equity-based sales to raise funds  sending the stock lower.💎Plantir  our AI darling  had a tough day and plunged nearly 10% after analysts shared that concerns over data ownership might reduce the ability of its analytics-software business to grow. This dampened sentiments on the recent good run of the stock.🎙Spotify Technologyhit the headlines for its staff layoffs. It is expected to reduce headcount by around 1500  which will be its third time of trimming this year. While shares have flipped by more than two times  the reduction hinted that management is concerned about future profit streams  given that they had expanded rapidly in recent years.🔋Major bitcoin miners likeMaraandRiotrose sharply  given the rise in BTC  which helped increase their margin.🚘Lastly  we haveUbershaking the storm as it rose in a red day after S&P Global said the stock has been rolled into the S&P 500 benchmark. The inclusion bodes well for stocks  as funds that track the index must buy the component.It is 7.45 am in Singapore and 7.45 pm in New York. December will be a challenging trading period  given the choppiness and consolidation of gains in November. Let us stay calm and look for opportunities.
